Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium orange-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Worn pencil, circled Name Armosilas. Trimmed. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR P.16043, which has the lettering straight in line 2.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0692)
